the result of the actors' hard work,)

90
00:06:25,479 --> 00:06:30,192
(and unauthorized filming is
strictly prohibited!)

91
00:06:48,691 --> 00:06:49,851
You're not scheduled for today.

92
00:06:49,852 --> 00:06:50,751
I know.

93
00:06:51,052 --> 00:06:52,671
I just dropped by to take a look.

94
00:06:53,251 --> 00:06:54,311
Are you that free?

95
00:06:55,532 --> 00:06:56,912
Guess cohabitation is pretty good, huh?

96
00:06:57,451 --> 00:06:58,832
What are you talking about?

97
00:06:59,052 --> 00:07:01,210
We talk show hosts follow
the code of ethics,

98
00:07:01,211 --> 00:07:02,272
okay?

99
00:07:02,292 --> 00:07:03,370
The first one being,

100
00:07:03,371 --> 00:07:05,171
no improper relationships with fans.

101
00:07:05,172 --> 00:07:06,051
Okay, okay.

102
00:07:06,052 --> 00:07:07,570
He's not your fan anyway.

103
00:07:07,571 --> 00:07:09,272
No need to feel pressured.

104
00:07:13,451 --> 00:07:14,392
Guan Xingxin?

105
00:07:16,371 --> 00:07:17,191
Yu Dule.

106
00:07:17,652 --> 00:07:18,472
Liang Daiwen.

107
00:07:19,211 --> 00:07:20,232
You guys know one another?

108
00:07:25,451 --> 00:07:26,792
Didn't expect to see you again.

109
00:07:28,211 --> 00:07:29,311
Perfect.

110
00:07:30,371 --> 00:07:31,392
Here's your staff pass.

111
00:07:32,211 --> 00:07:33,712
I broke up with Chen Yijin.

112
00:07:33,732 --> 00:07:34,871
Thank you for your help,

113
00:07:35,211 --> 00:07:36,871
although I'm not sure
what your motive was.

114
00:07:37,251 --> 00:07:38,250
You probably also think

115
00:07:38,251 --> 00:07:40,130
that I'm a homewrecker.

116
00:07:40,131 --> 00:07:41,272
But I swear,

117
00:07:41,412 --> 00:07:43,551
I was the last person
to know that he has a wife.

118
00:07:44,131 --> 00:07:45,751
If your intention was to ridicule me,

119
00:07:46,412 --> 00:07:47,712
well, you got your wish.

120
00:07:49,451 --> 00:07:51,191
I never wanted to ridicule you.

121
00:07:52,251 --> 00:07:53,392
Neither did I expect

122
00:07:53,492 --> 00:07:55,472
things to get to this point.

123
00:07:56,292 --> 00:07:57,152
I'm sorry.

124
00:08:03,412 --> 00:08:05,311
Hello everyone, I'm Daodao.

125
00:08:06,412 --> 00:08:07,690
I have a PhD in Chemistry.

126
00:08:07,691 --> 00:08:09,712
Many people think
that chemicals are poisonous.

127
00:08:09,771 --> 00:08:11,291
When they're promoting their products,

128
00:08:11,292 --> 00:08:13,040
they say they're without
any chemical components.

129
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:15,690
The most ridiculous instance
was of a pesticide.

130
00:08:15,691 --> 00:08:17,912
They claimed it did not contain
any chemicals.

131
00:08:18,652 --> 00:08:19,912
Won't you go on stage today?

132
00:08:20,451 --> 00:08:21,971
Guys, are they wanting to suicide?

133
00:08:21,972 --> 00:08:22,991
No.

134
00:08:24,092 --> 00:08:25,751
My boss caught me

135
00:08:25,852 --> 00:08:27,232
stealing the video.

136
00:08:27,492 --> 00:08:29,472
She almost made me become
a full-time talk show host.

137
00:08:30,211 --> 00:08:31,171
So I'm calling it quits.

138
00:08:31,172 --> 00:08:33,031
What do you think you're drinking?
Coca Cola?

139
00:08:33,691 --> 00:08:35,271
If it's because of Guan Xingxin,

140
00:08:35,652 --> 00:08:36,832
you needn't be so worried.

141
00:08:37,691 --> 00:08:38,952
She's not close with your boss.

142
00:08:40,211 --> 00:08:41,051
I can tell,

143
00:08:41,052 --> 00:08:42,232
she's closer to you.

144
00:08:44,851 --> 00:08:46,352
But she's not my girlfriend.

145
00:08:46,932 --> 00:08:48,192
We've never dated.

146
00:09:03,532 --> 00:09:04,391
My daughter.

147
00:09:04,611 --> 00:09:06,592
Why did you only pick up my call now?

148
00:09:07,691 --> 00:09:08,490
Go on.

149
00:09:08,491 --> 00:09:09,472
What's up?

150
00:09:09,652 --> 00:09:10,791
Nothing major.

151
00:09:11,052 --> 00:09:12,271
I just wanted to tell you,

152
00:09:12,611 --> 00:09:14,111
the pair that's renting your room

153
00:09:14,172 --> 00:09:15,151
has been chased out.

154
00:09:15,292 --> 00:09:16,051
It's just not right.

155
00:09:16,052 --> 00:09:17,850
They were fighting
and started brandishing knives.

156
00:09:17,851 --> 00:09:19,271
It was so scary.

157
00:09:20,091 --> 00:09:20,911
What?

158
00:09:21,451 --> 00:09:22,791
You're not hurt, are you?

159
00:09:24,091 --> 00:09:25,672
Oh, I'm not hurt.

160
00:09:26,292 --> 00:09:27,432
It's just that,

161
00:09:27,491 --> 00:09:29,352
your wall is covered

162
00:09:29,491 --> 00:09:30,631
in blood

163
00:09:31,372 --> 00:09:33,610
Mom, can you not take gulps of air
while speaking?

164
00:09:33,611 --> 00:09:35,151
You really scared me.

165
00:09:35,252 --> 00:09:36,312
As for the wall,

166
00:09:36,331 --> 00:09:37,832
give it a coat of paint.

167
00:09:38,172 --> 00:09:39,810
Still, I should let you know.

168
00:09:39,811 --> 00:09:41,411
In case you suddenly

169
00:09:41,412 --> 00:09:42,391
came back.

170
00:09:42,652 --> 00:09:43,791
You'd be shocked.

171
00:09:46,252 --> 00:09:47,432
Dear Meixia.

172
00:09:48,331 --> 00:09:50,391
Are you perhaps missing me?

173
00:09:51,091 --> 00:09:52,192
Of course not.

174
00:09:52,451 --> 00:09:54,232
I'm enjoying the peace
and quiet at home.

175
00:09:55,571 --> 00:09:57,871
Okay, sure. But I'm missing you.

176
00:09:58,611 --> 00:10:00,911
I'll find a time to ask my boss
for a break

177
00:10:00,932 --> 00:10:01,871
so I can go back to see you.

178
00:10:04,052 --> 00:10:05,352
It's a deal then.

179
00:11:22,372 --> 00:11:24,232
Did I wake you up?

180
00:11:25,211 --> 00:11:26,051
Sorry about that.

181
00:11:26,052 --> 00:11:27,712
I'm packing my luggage.

182
00:11:28,052 --> 00:11:29,072
I can tell.

183
00:11:29,652 --> 00:11:31,352
Your packing skills
are as awful as ever.

184
00:11:36,052 --> 00:11:38,151
When you open your bag at home,

185
00:11:38,932 --> 00:11:41,160
your mom might just think you
were scavenging in the East China Sea.

186
00:11:42,772 --> 00:11:43,531
When I moved,

187
00:11:43,532 --> 00:11:45,511
I should've packed a whetstone

188
00:11:45,731 --> 00:11:47,271
and grind your mouth a little.

189
00:11:48,372 --> 00:11:49,312
How long will you be gone?

190
00:11:50,372 --> 00:11:51,151
Why?

191
00:11:51,571 --> 00:11:53,271
Are you going to feel lost without me?

192
00:11:57,052 --> 00:11:57,931
If it's less than a week,

193
00:11:57,932 --> 00:11:59,751
you don't need so many pairs of shoes.

194
00:12:01,851 --> 00:12:03,651
I think at most it'd be

195
00:12:03,652 --> 00:12:04,672
a couple of days.

196
00:12:05,211 --> 00:12:08,031
Truth is, I haven't asked my boss
about the leave yet.

197
00:12:09,611 --> 00:12:10,631
Don't you have annual leave?

198
00:12:12,451 --> 00:12:13,712
Mr. Liang,

199
00:12:13,892 --> 00:12:15,531
not every person is like you,

200
00:12:15,532 --> 00:12:17,271
able to get all your leave approved.

201
00:12:19,731 --> 00:12:21,511
And not everyone is like you,

202
00:12:22,172 --> 00:12:23,192
having a family to go back to.

203
00:12:29,292 --> 00:12:31,312
My family isn't all that great.

204
00:12:32,172 --> 00:12:33,871
My parents divorced a long time ago.

205
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:36,111
I was brought up solely by my mom.

206
00:12:36,932 --> 00:12:38,651
She's a typical

207
00:12:38,652 --> 00:12:40,391
free and easy kind of person.

208
00:12:40,772 --> 00:12:42,490
She drinks, gets into fights,

209
00:12:42,491 --> 00:12:44,271
has no care for public order and morals.

210
00:12:44,892 --> 00:12:46,011
She married my dad

211
00:12:46,012 --> 00:12:47,330
all because of a plate

212
00:12:47,331 --> 00:12:48,871
of dumplings with egg and chive filling.

213
00:12:50,012 --> 00:12:51,631
She couldn't eat eggs before.

214
00:12:51,731 --> 00:12:53,592
So my dad very confidently assured her,

215
00:12:53,932 --> 00:12:55,210
if you're willing to marry me,

216
00:12:55,211 --> 00:12:56,712
you'll have enough eggs
to last a lifetime.

217
00:12:57,851 --> 00:12:58,730
Later,

218
00:12:58,731 --> 00:13:01,312
they hardly had any time
to think about eggs.

219
00:13:01,971 --> 00:13:04,672
My mom worked day and night
to support my education.

220
00:13:05,772 --> 00:13:07,151
It was pretty bad back then.

221
00:13:08,172 --> 00:13:09,832
But my mom always sees the bright side.

222
00:13:11,172 --> 00:13:13,232
She was working at a factory then.

223
00:13:13,892 --> 00:13:15,991
I'd wait for her to get off work
at the parking lot entrance.

224
00:13:16,491 --> 00:13:19,832
One time, an old pervert touched my leg.

225
00:13:20,971 --> 00:13:22,931
My mom immediately took out a saw

226
00:13:22,932 --> 00:13:24,552
and whacked the guy's leg.

227
00:13:25,532 --> 00:13:26,570
As a result,

228
00:13:26,571 --> 00:13:28,210
both she and the tool

229
00:13:28,211 --> 00:13:30,031
got taken to the police station.

230
00:13:31,652 --> 00:13:32,991
At the time, I thought to myself,

231
00:13:33,412 --> 00:13:34,911
when I grow up,

232
00:13:35,252 --> 00:13:37,232
I won't ever let my mom suffer again.

233
00:14:00,412 --> 00:14:01,352
Liang Daiwen.

234
00:14:03,971 --> 00:14:05,352
Liang Daiwen!

235
00:15:12,731 --> 00:15:13,371
Ma'am.

236
00:15:13,372 --> 00:15:14,391
You're back, Gu Yi.

237
00:15:32,052 --> 00:15:33,151
Mrs. Meixia.

238
00:15:33,412 --> 00:15:35,352
Is this what you called
"covered in blood"?

239
00:15:36,532 --> 00:15:38,171
No matter the amount, it's still blood.

240
00:15:38,172 --> 00:15:39,192
It's gross.

241
00:15:41,611 --> 00:15:42,352
Coming.

242
00:15:53,172 --> 00:15:53,651
Look at you.

243
00:15:53,652 --> 00:15:55,271
Why did you pack so much stuff again?

244
00:15:55,971 --> 00:15:57,991
You're almost out of rice
at home, right?

245
00:15:58,172 --> 00:15:59,751
I got some more for you.

246
00:16:01,372 --> 00:16:02,771
I found this at the market.

247
00:16:02,772 --> 00:16:04,690
It's the old-school cake
you're able to eat.

248
00:16:04,691 --> 00:16:06,072
I bought you two catty's worth.

249
00:16:06,292 --> 00:16:08,051
I haven't paid you for the fish
you brought last time.

250
00:16:08,052 --> 00:16:09,072
You're spending too much.

251
00:16:09,532 --> 00:16:11,251
Well, I basically polished off

252
00:16:11,252 --> 00:16:13,072
all the fried hairtail you made.

253
00:16:13,971 --> 00:16:15,991
There's no need to talk about money
between us.

254
00:16:18,892 --> 00:16:20,072
Are you Yi?

255
00:16:20,412 --> 00:16:21,552
Hello, sir.

256
00:16:29,052 --> 00:16:30,031
Who's that?

257
00:16:30,772 --> 00:16:31,832
He Yunjun.

258
00:16:32,252 --> 00:16:34,031
He used to be a member
of the same drama club.

259
00:16:34,491 --> 00:16:35,631
The one who acted as Justice Bao.

260
00:16:35,652 --> 00:16:37,271
You had called him Uncle Dark Skin
back then.

261
00:17:01,892 --> 00:17:03,111
You've eaten,

262
00:17:03,292 --> 00:17:04,311
watched your drama.

263
00:17:04,852 --> 00:17:05,751
Let's begin then.

264
00:17:07,852 --> 00:17:08,712
Begin what?

265
00:17:11,531 --> 00:17:13,472
We've done many sessions.

266
00:17:13,812 --> 00:17:15,271
Could you be a little more

267
00:17:15,491 --> 00:17:16,432
self-aware?

268
00:17:29,652 --> 00:17:31,071
She's currently living in my house.

269
00:17:33,612 --> 00:17:34,311
Who?

270
00:17:36,372 --> 00:17:37,791
The talk show artist?

271
00:17:38,572 --> 00:17:39,351
She has a name.

272
00:17:40,612 --> 00:17:41,311
Gu Yi.

273
00:17:44,451 --> 00:17:45,392
Liang Daiwen.

274
00:17:46,332 --> 00:17:47,751
You should know

275
00:17:47,852 --> 00:17:49,371
that you're in no state to get involved

276
00:17:49,372 --> 00:17:51,071
in an intimate relationship right now.

